4.3. Adding the LFS User 
Minty benc # groupadd lfs
Minty benc # useradd -s /bin/bash -g lfs -m -k /dev/null lfs
Minty benc # passwd lfs
Enter new UNIX password: 
Retype new UNIX password: 
passwd: password updated successfully
Minty benc # chown -v lfs $LFS/tools
changed ownership of '/mnt/lfs/tools' from root to lfs
Minty benc # chown -v lfs $LFS/sources
changed ownership of '/mnt/lfs/sources' from root to lfs
Minty benc # su - lfs
lfs@Minty ~ $ 

